Bombay Palace Restaurants Inc, with itsemphasis on location and low food costs, expects its 1987 salesto increase 150 pct to about 22 mln dlrs from about 8.5 mlndlrs in 1986, according to President Sant S. Chatwal.     Chatwal told members of the Dallas financial community ata lunchtime briefing, "we go for prime locations everywhere andmake sure our leases are very favorable."     As previously announced, the company expects to report1986 earnings of about 700,000 dlrs, or 31 to 33 cts a share,on revenues of 8.5 mln dlrs. Chatwal said the final figureswould be released in about two days. Reuter&#3;